-- Indonesia Stocks: Bakrieland, Bank Internasional, Semen Gresik
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-01-17T09:25:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/indonesia-stock-movers-astra-bank-internasional-semen-gresik.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 1.2 percent to 3,954.76,
the highest close since Sept. 9.  Rubber producers:  PT Bakrie Sumatera Plantations (UNSP)  
increased 5.1 percent to 310 rupiah, the biggest gain since Nov.
2.  PT Perusahaan Perkebunan London Sumatra Indonesia (LSIP)  ,
the nation’s second-largest listed plantation company by market
value, rose 3.1 percent to 2,475 rupiah. Rubber futures advanced
to the highest level in more than five weeks, adding 3.8 percent
to settle at 291 yen a kilogram ($3,796 a metric ton) in  Tokyo .  PT Bakrieland Development (ELTY)  , a property developer,
gained 7.4 percent to 146 rupiah, the highest close since Sept.
7. Bakrieland expects 2011 revenue growth to have exceeded its
estimate of 30 percent, Corporate Secretary Nuzirman Nurdin said
today.  PT Bank Internasional Indonesia (BNII)  , a unit of
Malaysia’s biggest bank by assets, Malayan Banking Bhd., jumped
12 percent to 470 rupiah, its steepest increase since Dec. 9,
2010. Shareholders approved the appointment of Khairussaleh
Ramli, chief financial officer of Malayan Banking, as president
director of Bank Internasional.  PT Semen Gresik (SMGR)  ,  Indonesia ’s largest cement
maker, climbed 2.6 percent to 11,850 rupiah, the highest close
since at least August 1991. The company may build a cement plant
in Kalimantan in 2014 or 2015,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing
Agung Wiharto, investor relations officer at the company.
Wiharto couldn’t be reached when called at his office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
